[http://www.zuloark.com The Zuloark Collective] is a group of architects, designers, builders and thinkers operating within the fields of architecture, urbanism, design, pedagogies, research and development.

zuloark has been recognized nationally and internationally with awards including the Golden Nica (2013) granted Barley Field, second and third prize in Europan IX or Arquia / Next Award (2012) developed within a Collective Intelligence Platform Zoohaus and has been a finalist in the XI Biennial of Spanish Architecture and Urbanism (Gran Vía / Great Work).

Zuloark is linked to the construction of open networking infrastructure. They were among the prime movers in the regeneration of the [[La Latina Neighborhood in Madrid|La Latina neighbourhood in Madrid]] and the [[El Campo de Cebada/es|Campo de Cebada]].